The paper discusses reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The focus is on model-based reinforcement learning, which involves building a model of the environment. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper deals with optimization and regularization, which are common topics in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the interaction between the agent and the environment, which is a key aspect of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents different approaches to mitigate planner overfitting, which involves statistical techniques and regularization, suggesting that the paper could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category.
